---
const points = [
  {
    n: "01",
    title: "No app-store dance",
    body: "Drivers don't download anything. There's nothing for IT to provision, approve, or refuse. Opening a link is something every driver already knows how to do.",
  },
  {
    n: "02",
    title: "Updates ship instantly",
    body: "Push a fix at 09:00, every device runs it before lunch. No \"old version stuck on Bob's phone\" problem. No version skew between roles.",
  },
  {
    n: "03",
    title: "One codebase, every device",
    body: "iOS, Android, Windows, macOS, ChromeOS — and the yard's dusty kiosk PC. Less native overhead means packages start at £79/month.",
  },
];
---

<section id="why-pwa" class="relative bg-[color:var(--color-graphite)] text-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-amber)]">Why a PWA</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight">
        Adoption friction near-zero. By design.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/70 text-lg">
        The Progressive Web App delivery model is the foundational design choice Fleetlix is built around.
        Every other decision flows from it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      {points.map((p) => (
        <div class="relative">
          <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-extrabold text-7xl text-[color:var(--color-amber)]/70 leading-none">
            {p.n}
          </span>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-bold text-2xl text-white">{p.title}</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-white/70 leading-relaxed">{p.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
